article.headline: Youngstown State 20, Illinois State 17
article.story:
YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Palmer kicked two field goals in
the fourth quarter to give Youngstown State a 20-17 win over
Illinois State on Saturday.

Marcus Mason rushed for 126 yards and a touchdown for the
Penguins (4-1, 1-0 Gateway Conference).

Brian Thompson finished with 122 yards rushing for Illinois
State (3-2, 0-1), which had 227 yards on the ground. The Redbirds
outgained the Penguins 407-311 but quarterback Luke Drone threw
four interceptions.

Palmer's 26-yard kick with 6:04 left tied the game at 17. His
kick from 21 yards with 3:52 remaining got the Penguins the lead.
Both field goals came after Drone interceptions.

Mason ran 26 yards for a score and Kevin Mazur booted a 24-yard
field goal to help Illinois State build a 10-7 lead at halftime.

Tom Zetts threw a 21-yard touchdown pass to Kyle Smith early in
the third quarter to get the Penguins a 14-10 lead. Zetts finished
13-for-26 for 171 yards with two interceptions while Smith had
seven receptions for 97 yards and a score.

Illinois State drove to the Youngstown State 40-yard line after
the Penguins took the lead but Joe Juby intercepted a Drone pass.
The Penguins then ran out the clock.

Rafael Bice also ran for 65 yards and a touchdown for Illinois
State.
